==Russian==

===Origins===
The expression originated after the character of hardworking [[woodcarver]] Carlo from the popular children's motion picture "Приключения Буратино" (The Adventures of Buratino), 1975, based on the novel "The Little Gold Key or the Adventures of Buratino" by [[:w:Aleksey Nikolayevich Tolstoy|Aleksey Tolstoy]], which, in turn, is an adaptation of "The Adventures of Pinocchio" by [[:w:Carlo Collodi|Carlo Collodi]]. 

===Idiom===
'''[[работать]], [[как]] [[папа]] Карло'''
# to work hard (literally, ''to work like papa Carlo''). 
#:Пока вы тут прохлаждаетесь, мне приходится работать, как папа Карло. — While you are idling here, I have to toil out.

====Variants====
*'''[[вкалывать]], как папа Карло'''
*'''[[пахать]], как папа Карло'''

